                            <comment id="13437594" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 19 Aug 2012 22:01:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried to create a test case, but for some reason it doesn&apos;t seem to have the same behavior as the example above...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437602" author="jun_o" created="Sun, 19 Aug 2012 22:56:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;maybe related issues, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3502&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3502&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3657&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3657&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437611" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 19 Aug 2012 23:59:16 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I tried to create a test case, but for some reason it doesn&apos;t seem to have the same behavior as the example above...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ah, OK - if real-time get retrieves the fields from the tlog, copyfields will not have been run yet.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems like we should prevent real-time get from returning copyfield targets when retrieved from the index.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437627" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Mon, 20 Aug 2012 02:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that seems to fix things by not returning copyField targets in real-time get.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437657" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Mon, 20 Aug 2012 04:25:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should also consider changing author_s to author_facet (i.e. an indexed-only dynamic string field).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13478226" author="danacohen01" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2012 18:46:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is still an issue for me. i can reproduce the same as above without explicitly using real-time get or solr cloud.&lt;br/&gt;
this may need to be reopened?&lt;/p&gt;

